description: Azriel, the Servant of the Bones, continues his tale as he confronts the leader of The Temple of The Mind, Gregory Belkin. This charismatic cult leader's execution of his step-daughter brought Azriel to present day NYC for vengeance, but its meeting Esther Belkin's mother, Rachel, that teaches him about earthly love.

They're an all-new team, banded together to battle evil and injustice, bearing the name of their predecessors.

They're not the strongest, but they are the only hope in the final battle against the greatest enemies of mankind. They are...

THE LAST AVENGERS

United they will fall.
name: TPB

volume.name: Little Orphan Annie: Home at Last
Edgar Rice Burroughs Tarzan of the Apes

name: Die Grune Lanterne: Terra Soll Sterben
This Is My Life by Bob Hope

description: Told here within this publication are the Jack London short stories of 'Chinago', 'The Death of Lingoun', and 'Told in the Drooling Ward'. Each Jack London short story is illustrated by well-known comic veterans Guy Davis (B.P.R.D./Hellboy), Vince Locke (Sandman/Deadworld), and Charles Yates.

Double sized issue. Experience the next level of consciousness...the level where dreams blend with reality, where the power of the mind manifests imagination, where a mere thought can bring salvation...or death. Beyond the level of dream, further than the realm of imagination, it is Level X. Six test subjects are plunged into a living nightmare as they are sucked into the memory of a super computer during dream analysis testing. Together they find themselves thrown into the very dreams of their counterparts and soon learn that even death exists in this new level of dreaming. The technicians and scientists of the LeMarc Foundation, the organization behind the testing, begin a frantic struggle to capture the consciousness of the subjects. Can they succeed and bring them back?

Working from ideas developed by Vaughn Bodé right before his death, his son Mark has re-enlisted his father's entire cast of characters for The Lizard of Oz, a full-color graphic novel that pays playful homage to and parodies the classic L. Frank Baum fairy tale (and its beloved film adaptation). Blessed with an original full-color wraparound cover by Vaughn Bodé (one of his last completed works), augmented with a long introduction by Bodé expert and Paper magazine contributor Carlo McCormick that explores the legacies of both Bodé and Oz creator L. Frank Baum, as well as with a sketchbook of Mark's preparatory work for this ambitious book.
name: Bode's Lizard of Oz

description: Diabolik meets Eva, and is love at first sight. But Diabolik is arrested by Inspector Ginko, tried and sentenced to guillotine. Just a few hours from the execution, when all seems already lost, Eva saves him from certain death. Now for her and Diabolik is the beginning of a wonderful love, that is still ongoing.
name: L'arresto di Diabolik

description:
What is the connection between the mysterious "Elsewhere" base with the enterprise of the I Mille?

July 1860. Under the command of an army of volunteers, Giuseppe Garibaldi takes control of Sicily and is preparing to land on the Italian mainland to continue the conquest of the South in the name of Victor Emmanuel II of Savoy . But the company of the Thousand suffers a setback when the Strait of Messina is locked up by a naval blockade ordered by King Francis of Bourbon , with the help of France. The eyes of the world are focused on Italy, since the turn of events will take affect the balance of Europe. But at "Altrove" - the secret American base where every kind of paranormal phenomenon is studied - they have a different kind of concern: it seems that a sinister character who intends to manipulate events for their own ends personalisi is moving in the shadows. To save the future, "Altrove" therefore puts in a fascinating field agent from the mysterious past, to gain collaboration of the only man who can - perhaps - give an answer to all the mysteries: the composer Giuseppe Verdi
name: La donna che cambiò la Storia d'Italia

description: Jerusalem. A rabbi is killed under mysterious circumstances, and simultaneously two of his fellows in Europe meet the same tragic end. What is the link between the victims? A Master of Jewish tradition calls for the collaboration of Martin Mystère, but he is in hospital, unable to move. For one time, it's up to Diana to play the role of the "Detective of the Impossible" and to solve the riddle.
name: Il verdetto di Cassiopea

description:
Something is watching us: it’s ready to strike and is hiding in the shadows!

Sometimes we see them at the “corner” of our eyes: shadows, tiny specks, vague shapes that disappear as soon as we focus on them to identify their nature. Is it just an optical phenomenon, as we usually think, or is there somebody or something that follows us, watching us from the dark, ready to strike? When, during a blackout, Inspector Travis mysteriously disappears from the police station, it’s Martin Mystère’s time to pursue the investigation that his policeman friend was following. A case of murder, already closed at first sight, where the culprit is locked up in an insane asylum... and he sees things other people can’t see!
name: Con la coda dell'occhio

description: The Grim Ghost, Phoenix, Wulf the Barbarian, and Detective Sam Lomax join forces for the first time in 35 years in a historical Atlas crossover event! Which enemy could make these Atlas Heroes set aside their differences, forge an alliance, and risk everything to defeat it?
name: Midnight
